# State Management (Riverpod)

## Prefer reactive providers for DB-derived state

Database-derived state must be a `StreamProvider` driven by Drift `watch()` /
`dashboardChanges()`, NOT a `FutureProvider` that callers remember to invalidate.
A `FutureProvider` here caused stale net-worth totals after add/delete.

```dart
// GOOD: recomputes automatically on any relevant write
final homeSummaryProvider = StreamProvider<HomeSummary>((ref) {
  final settings = ref.watch(settingsProvider).valueOrNull;
  if (settings == null) return const Stream<HomeSummary>.empty();
  final db = ref.watch(databaseProvider);
  return _watchDashboard(db, () => _computeHomeSummary(...));
});
```

After a mutation, do NOT sprinkle `ref.invalidate(...)`; the stream providers
update themselves once the write commits.

## Display currency

Read the display currency from `displayCurrencyProvider` — never re-inline
`ref.watch(settingsProvider).when(...)` in each widget.

```dart
final display = ref.watch(displayCurrencyProvider); // falls back to CNY while loading
```

## Compute once

Compute expensive aggregates (e.g. `familyTrend`, forecasts) once and pass the
result down to child widgets instead of recomputing per widget.
